{"id": "g7jb1c", "title": "What to do when market keeps moving higher?", "selftext": "In the past 2 weeks, what we saw is very much different from what we expected:\n\n* Oil crashed on low demand.\n* Sky-high unemployment numbers.\n* Mixed earning calls and withdrawal of guidances.\n* Treasury yields still gets lower.\n* Lower volumes.\n\nBut:\n\n* Equities push higher.\n* VIX below 50 and still going lower.\n* SPY establishes a strong support at 250 early April and trading within 269-290 with no sign of stopping.\n\nMy assumptions are:\n\n* The stimulus/bond buying money is flowing into the equity market.\n* Companies are now prepared and have liquidity to last 2 more quarters without substantial business.\n* Q1 earnings don't fully capture the picture.\n* Pessimistically, the country will start opening up again around mid-June with some guidelines.\n* There will be sector rotation out of tech into travel and finance.\n\nWith those in minds:\n\n* Oil demand for June/July should be stable/goes up.\n* It is hard to see another leg down before Q2 earnings (June-July), when people fully comprehend the damage on the economy as a whole.\n\nHence, the plan is to capture some profits before the rotation happens:\n\n* Cash secured puts for travel/finance (weekly or monthly)\n* Covered call on tech stocks.\n* Bullish put credit spread for QQQ and SPY with mid June expiration.\n\nBecause VIX is getting lower, we also:\n\n* Adding puts for June/July (250-270)", "created_utc": 1587771735.0, "permalink": "/r/wallstreetbets/comments/g7jb1c/what_to_do_when_market_keeps_moving_higher/", "is_self": true}